pend Eternity in &s;uch a Sepa|ration, and immen&s;ely different Circum&s;tances! And that howe|ver you have been intimately acquainted and nearly related, clo&s;e-un<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">ed and mutually conver&s;ant here in this World; and how much &s;oever you have taken Delight in each other's Company! Shall it be &s;o after you have been together a great While, each of you in undoing your&s;elves, enh<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">&s;ing your Guilt, and heaping up <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">rath, that their &s;o wi&s;ely changing their Minds, and their Cour&s;e, and choo&s;ing &s;uch Happine&s;s for them&s;elves, &s;hould now at length be the beginning of &s;uch an exceeding and everla&s;ting Separation between you and them? How awful wi<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">l it be to be parted &s;o!</P>
<P N="3">3 Con&s;ider the great Encouragement that God gives you, ear|ne&s;tly to &s;trive for the &s;ame ble&s;&s;ing that Others have obtained. There is great Encouragement in the Word of God to Sinners, to &s;eek Salvation; in the Revelation that we have of the abundant Provi&s;ion made for the Salvation even of the ch<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">f of Sinners, and in the Appointment of &s;o many <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">leans to be u&s;ed with and by Sinners, in order to their Salvation; and by the Ble&s;&s;ing which God in his Word connects with the Means of his Appointment. There is hence great Encouragements for a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">&punc; <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">t all <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">imes, that will be thorough in u&s;ing of the&s;e <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word">. But now God gives extraordin<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">y Encouragement in his Providence by pouring out his Spirit &s;o remarkably unto g<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">t us, and bringing &s;avingly Home to him&s;elf&punc; all Sorts, young and old, rich and poor, wi&s;e and unwi&s;e&punc; &s;ober and vicious, of &s;elf righteous Seekers, and profli|gate Livers; &mdash;no Sort are exempt There is now at this Day, among&s;t us, the loude&s;t Ca<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">l, and the greate&s;t Encouragement, &amp; the wide&s;t Door opened to Sinners, to e&s;cape out of a State of Sin and Condemnation, that perhaps God <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ver granted in New-<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="6 letters">d.
